  <Subject Subject_ID="300218855">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300217891</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>ball striking or snaring and throwing equipment [300217891], ball game equipment [300211062], sports and athletic equipment [300211035], recreational artifacts (equipment) [300218781], Recreational Artifacts (hierarchy name) [300136012], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Any of various short-handled objects with wide, rounded heads, usually primarily of wood designed for various ball games. For similar-shaped but usually larger objects with heads containing netting, use "rackets (sports equipment)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para cualquiera de varios objetos de mangos cortos y cabezas anchas y redondas, y en su origen diseñadas generalmente de madera para diversos juegos de pelota. Para objetos de forma similar, pero generalmente más largos con cabezas encerrando una malla o red, use "raqueta (equipamiento deportivo)”.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor diverse voorwerpen met korte stelen en brede, geronde koppen, meestal hoofdzakelijk van hout en ontworpen voor verschillende balspelen. Gebruik 'rackets (sportuitrusting)' voor grotere voorwerpen met een soortgelijke vorm maar met koppen met een netwerk.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gerät mit kurzem Griff und breitem, abgerundetem Kopf, in der Regel aus Holz, mit dem der Ball in verschiedenen Sportarten geschlagen wird. Für ähnlich geformte, doch größere Geräte dieser Art, deren Kopf ein in einen Rahmen gespanntes Netzgeflecht ist, wird der Begriff "Racket" verwendet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
